##New champion pneumonia cured: Experience Life after death, more love life

The papernews

The function introduction, has the connotation the current politics new media

Zhu Ying, Zhong Xiaomei, Ming Que, intern, Liu Yuxiu, _ paper _ journalist

Li Zhendong and illness struggle 16 days later finally cured discharged from hospital, he hopes his experience can provide reference for patients. REPORTER: Yan Hailong, Wei Fan, editor: Zeng Yiwen, video source: thepaper.cn 04:53

This winter, new pneumonia is sweeping across much of the country. One person feels as if he has a cold, another has several degrees of respiratory failure, as if he has died.

As of 19:00 on February 12,44,763 people had been diagnosed with NCP, 1115 had died and 4870 had been cured.

Among the confirmed cases, the youngest was born in Wuhan just 30 hours ago, and the oldest was a 97-year-old woman in Nanjing. Among the cured patients, the youngest was 9 months old, and both were infected when their parents traveled from Wuhan to Beijing. The oldest was a 91-year-old mother-in-law from Yichang, Hubei, who recovered after 15 days in hospital.

Behind each number is a story of living life, fighting disease and struggling to survive. They are parents, children, market merchants, taxi drivers, medical personnel... depending on perseverance and resistance, some people carry over the erosion of the virus, breathe the breath of freedom; More people are holding out, waiting for the epidemic to die down.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Area 1, Department of Critical Care Medicine, Zhongnan Hospital, Wuhan University

Decreased resistance

On January 10, Li drove from Jingzhou to Wuhan on a business trip to attend a conference and have dinner with friends in the evening. At 37, he works a lot, travels a lot, and doesn't fall asleep until 11 or 12 p.m.

When he returned to Jingzhou the next day, he felt feverish. He went to the hospital on the 12th, and his temperature was over 100 degrees. When the blood report came back, the doctor's initial assessment was upper respiratory tract infection.

At the time, new coronary pneumonia was a news flash for him. As there is no weakness in the limbs, cough, chest tightness and other symptoms, he thought it was the flu, for fear of infection to the family, put on a mask, isolated in a room at home.

He wore a mask when he went to work. Two days later, on the night of the 14th, he developed a violent cough and chest tightness and went to the emergency department for a CT scan. Seeing the report of the shadow in his lung, the doctor said it might be tuberculosis, so he was immediately transferred to the Chest Hospital of Jingzhou City in Hubei Province for isolation.

It was nearly 12 o'clock at night, and the doctor on duty at the hospital asked him about his schedule and health from the 10th.

Not only was the hospital well equipped, but he could feel the tension. It wasn't until he walked into the room and saw the machines beside his bed and countless tests that he realized how serious this was.

Li Zhendong was not the only one who took it lightly. Even the medical staff was not spared.

On January 5, Doctor Huang Huxiang received the first fever patient after the New Year in the aspiration department, the other side is more than 50 years old, lung lesions. Before he knew about the new coronavirus, he thought it was a common viral pneumonia.

Around January 15, his Central Huanggang Hospital in Hubei Province was set up as a designated hospital, with more patients every day. Huanggang City Center for Disease Control to sample. After that, the smoking doctor began wearing an N95 mask and disposable surgical clothing.

He later recalled that during that time, many patients, may accidentally contact with infected patients, and often work overtime, resistance has decreased. Before Huang's infection, two nurses and one doctor were infected among the 24 medical staff in his department.

Guo Qin, a nurse in the emergency center of Zhongnan Hospital of Wuhan University, was the first hospital worker to contract the infection.

At the end of December, Guo learned that pneumonia of unknown origin had been discovered in Wuhan. A few days later, the hospital also issued a notice, for fever patients have a set of special procedures, to give patients masks, registration information.

Since the beginning of January, more and more patients have come to the hospital with fever. The hospital has converted an isolation ward in the emergency ward for patients with new symptoms of coronary pneumonia. Fifteen beds were quickly filled, and two or three more were added.

It was also a time of high incidence of influenza and heart and brain diseases. On Jan. 6, a critically ill patient in his 50s arrived at the hospital, and Guo took part in the emergency treatment. A week later, she had contact with four or five other patients who were later diagnosed. At that time, she worked more than ten hours a day, only four or five hours of sleep, she felt very tired, "resistance may not be enough. ".

Guo Qin's emergency center has 48 nurses, isolation ward has 10, adopt "three shift" mode, 2 people a group, every 5 days on a night shift. A person sometimes to take care of 6 critically ill patients, to help rescue, blood, transport, basic care, observation of illness, and so on, inevitably have close contact with the patient. Although everyone wore protective clothing, surgical masks and round hats, the risk of infection remained constant.

On January 12, Guo Qin presented with chills, fever symptoms, took antiviral drugs, the night she slept in a room, no longer contact with family. The next day, her fever reached 39 degrees and she was placed in isolation in the ward where she usually tended.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
The doctors'chest rooms, combined with imaging data, discuss each patient's condition.

The darkest hour of my life

At that time did not pass nucleic acid reagent to diagnose, the doctor is judged by CT Li Zhendong got new coronary pneumonia. "The hospital may have been trying to relieve my stress, telling me it was suspected, but I was actually in critical condition. " On the afternoon of the 15th, when he confirmed that he was being quarantined, his wife cried with worry.

At the time, there was only one confirmed case in Jingzhou, Hubei, of a south China seafood city porter. When Li Zhendong entered the isolation ward, the first case had already recovered nearly. Medical staff will also take the initiative to tell him the first case, has been consoling him that "can cure, no problem, do not worry. ". It gave him a confidence boost.

On his second day in the hospital, from 8 a.m. to 12 p.m. , he was constantly being given shots, pills, and tests.

In addition to chest films, CT, color ultrasound, he took a tube of blood in the morning, noon and evening, draw to two arms can not find a good place. The doctor takes a sample to test, still need him to cough up phlegm, but some patient of new coronary pneumonia has no phlegm, can dry cough only. "The person that cough is torn heart crack lung, cough out blood sometimes, see my in the mind straight hair is numb. " Li Zhendong recalls.

In order to supplement their physical strength, Li Zhendong every time after drawing blood to force himself to drink half a bottle of milk. Sometimes he coughed up blood and drank it, swallowing it with him.

There is no specific drug for npv pneumonia, so after hospitalization, antibiotics, antivirals, Gamma Globulin vials and traditional Chinese medicine prescribed by doctors should be administered daily according to the Hubei provincial treatment guidelines, Huang said.

On the evening of the 16th, he coughed all the time, took antiasthmatic and disease-controlling drugs, aerosolized, injected and breathed smoothly. The nurse gave him valium, adjusted the volume of the electrocardiograph, and turned off the lights to give him a break.

In the middle of the night, he claimed to have experienced a very dark and frightening moment in his life, because his congenital asthma had come on at the same time. "The fever was so high that I couldn't breathe. I coughed so hard and couldn't breathe. I felt myself babbling and losing consciousness. "

The nurse heard him come in moaning, but he was too weak to speak. The nurse took his temperature, 38.6 degrees. In his trance, he heard the nurse say, first drink warm water to observe body temperature, he did not want to drink, refused. Again the temperature has climbed to 39.1 degrees, the nurse said to feed drugs, hoping to reduce the fever, but he did not like the feeling of sweating, and refused.

Those days, Li Zhendong is still in the peak period of illness, every day high fever cough, can only rely on perseverance. He said that he could feel his body organs were beginning to fail, and he did not even have the strength to spit out the phlegm, "I'm not a fragile person, but I had tears in my eyes for a few days. When I collapsed, I was a little bit resistant to the hospital. Why do I get fluids every day, take medicine, and things still don't get better. "

Li Zhendong was touched that, despite his cough, the treatment of rejection, medical staff or risk infection, tirelessly for his supply of hot water, end shit end urine. "I drink about a thermos of boiling water a day, and when the thermos runs out, I call and the nurse fills it. "

Remember the first night in the hospital, Guo Qin Insomnia, ear ringing in the treatment cart moving sound, the sound of monitoring equipment, the nurses hurried footsteps. Usually partner's apprentice that night shift, said "you can not sleep, I come to see you at night" , several times to see her. That night she had five or six vials of anti-viral, anti-bacterial IV fluids.

This reminds Guo Qin of the previous night shift days, a night will go to each patient's bedside to observe how they breathe smoothly, sleep. Some mother-in-law to drink water, go to the toilet, also want to help take off pants, hold, even hold.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Central South Hospital medical staff in the care of patients.

"The race between the body and the virus. " "The triumph of the mind. "

Huang Huxiang stayed in the hospital for 15 days, the most serious days fever to 37.5 degrees, body pain, no energy, do not want to move, but consciousness is awake.

On the third or fourth day of his hospitalization, a former asthma patient heard of his illness and sent messages of prayer to his circle of friends, which gave him comfort.

Some people have been consulting him about the treatment and rehabilitation of his new coronary pneumonia. Whenever he is in better condition, he will reply in time, "They don't understand the disease, they have symptoms, like Bird on a Wire, and they're afraid they're going to die, so they still need to be educated and counseled. "

Liu Juan (not her real name) , 56, and her husband sell vegetables at three stalls at the West road market in Jiang'an District, four or five kilometers from the south China Seafood Market. It's only new year's. Take a week off.

For her, the first three days of treatment at Wuhan's fifth and Golden Pool hospitals after being diagnosed with new pneumonia were the hardest. "It's a nasty disease. It's very hard to breathe, it's very hard to breathe. "

When she first found out she had new pneumonia, she wasn't scared. When she saw the news on her mobile phone, she knew that the outbreak was serious. She could not sleep at night because of fear.

A few days before the hospital coma, body pain without appetite, she felt what is bitter to eat. On January 23rd, a bed doctor called her husband and said the disease could only boost a person's immunity and allow the body to race against the virus, "What if your wife doesn't eat or drink? Tell her to eat. This disease needs nutrition. How can you fight it if you have no resistance? "

Her husband rides his electric bike every day at noon to bring her porridge, vegetables, soup, milk, strawberries and security guards to bring them in. She found it hard to eat, so her husband added sugar to the Porridge.

Her husband, children and relatives call her every day to encourage her, "you will be fine, " "if you want to live, you must refuel, you must eat. ". She forced herself to eat it. Starting on the 27th, my pain is better, and I can finish my meal.

Adjacent bed an 82-year-old mother-in-law can not take care of herself, Liu Juan can get out of bed, often help her mother-in-law open the LID, pour water, take care of her. Mother-in-law is very touched, said "without you, I am hungry, " want to recognize her as a goddaughter, later mother-in-law first her a day out of the hospital.

Three days in hospital, colleagues every day sent a message to ask how Guo Qin condition, comfort her "do not worry, will be good" . Some colleagues stopped to come in to see her and tease her. Some bring her breakfast, send books, send flowers, flowers can not be brought into the ward, photos sent to her to encourage her to refuel. "I felt so warm at the time, " Guo said. "I cried in secret. "

Li, on the other hand, listens to audio programs and old songs on his cell phone. It gave A-do some strength when he finally broke down and listened to see it through. "The cough is very fierce when must use the willpower to control, otherwise easy to suffocate the stupor. I generally is suppresses after the cough slowly relaxes the body, the control inhales. "

The virus is a bully. Since January 23, Li Zhendong's high fever has subsided in a few days. On January 24, he began to enter the "recovery phase" . His cough is much better and his spirit is slowly recovering. He also asked a friend to buy some supplies to donate to the front-line medical workers.

He did not contact his family until he was better, but said nothing about his near-death experience. He was afraid that he might catch his breath or have a sudden change of situation. He only recorded videos of himself and sent them to his family. He did not dare to make instant video calls with them. His mother also cooked during this period sent to the hospital, put in a place, medical staff to help him. When he couldn't eat, he soaked the rice in soup and swallowed some of it.

He sat in his hospital bed, gasping and recording intermittent videos of his recovery, hoping that his presence would reassure some people who were sick or in fear.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Doctors and nurses use artificial membrane lung outside human body to replace the work of lung, so that patients can get adequate treatment and rest of their own lungs.

Discharge convalescence

After stopping the drug and staying in the hospital for observation for several days, Li Zhendong was discharged on January 31 after two negative nucleic acid tests. Doctors told him that there would be antibodies in the short term, but that his immune system would be compromised and he would be vulnerable to secondary infections, so he would be isolated at home for a period of time, during which he would need to eat light food and eat small meals.

The next day, he had a kind of "anesthetic awake" feeling, the internal organs have been in pain. That night, he had a fever of 102. The wife calls the doctor, and the attending says she's off her meds after she's discharged, and she's going through a physical adjustment period. It was nearly nine o'clock in the evening, the hospital pharmacy had closed, and the attending doctor had gone to fetch his medicine. After taking antipyretics and painkillers, his fever subsided the next morning and he recovered.

On the afternoon of February 3,17 days after her hospitalization, Liu Juan was discharged. A nurse said, "Auntie, you are out of the hospital today, congratulations, " she said gratefully, "you gave me a second life, I am grateful to you, not you, how can I today? "

The doctor did not give her medicine, but told her to rest at home, isolation at home for 14 days. When I went upstairs, I felt a little labored and out of breath, but it was better than when I was in the hospital, and I ate more. She wears a mask at home, too, keeping her distance from her husband and keeping the dishes separate.

On February 7, Guo Yanhong, commissioner of the Medical Administration and Hospital Authority of the National Health Commission, said that the number of cured patients has been increasing since January 30, according to the recent analysis of more than 500 discharged patients by experts organized by the Health Commission, the average length of stay of more than 500 cured patients was about 10 days.

For more than 4,000 healers, the lingering question is: Will there be a second infection or a hangover? Zhan Qingyuan, an expert at the china-japan Friendship Hospital, gave the answer: According to the General Law of virus infection, antibodies will be produced after infection, some of the antibodies may not last long, and patients are at risk of reinfection after cure, so protection should be strengthened, to prevent and treat colds, take appropriate activities at home. According to clinical experience, mild cases have no sequelae; severe cases may have left-over conditions such as pulmonary fibrosis over a period of time, most of which can be repaired in the end; very few severe cases may have left a little pulmonary fibrosis over a longer period of time, follow-up should be strengthened.

Guo returned to the forefront of the epidemic after 14 days of isolation after her discharge from the hospital. For the first two days she helped with medical advice and treatment, but the department was understaffed. On the third day she resumed her usual care of the critically ill. She lives in a house near the hospital and her husband visits her every other day. Returning to work has risks, but Guo Qin more "hope to cure the identity of the patient to tell everyone: Do not panic, to trust the medical staff. "

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Guo Qin, a nurse returning to work after recovering from new crown pneumonia. Photo courtesy of the respondents

Huang Hexiang often looked at the news of the epidemic during the quarantine. Around January 22, the hospital staff he knew were on the front line, along with medical teams from Shandong and Hunan, numbering more than 1,000 people, some of whom had not returned home for more than a month.

He wants to help. He wants to do his part. Colleagues sent him films, let him help to see the medical records, do remote consultation, "once saw a pregnant woman 25 weeks pregnant patients, this patient needs to be very careful medication, but later heard that the recovery is good. "

At this time, his seven-year-old children seem to suddenly grow up, understand the doctor's parents can not accompany her New Year is why.

On February 1st, the day of his release, the sun was shining. Huang took a shower, changed his clothes, put on a mask, and then contacted a community taxi to take him to his mother-in-law's empty room, isolated by himself. He had taken only seven days a year before, and said he had never taken such a long holiday. His advice to the healers for recovery at home: "Try not to go out, maintain indoor ventilation, wear a mask when you go out, wash your hands more often, it's crucial. Exercise at home, take rest, don't stay up late, and boost your immunity. "

On February 12, he returned to the hospital from quarantine to fight alongside his colleagues on the front lines of the epidemic.

Li Zhendong, who was discharged from the hospital the same day as Huang, now goes to bed at about 8:30 every night and wakes up around 6 a.m. When he wakes up, he'll be in his room doing stretches. Long-term immobility, legs, arms feel a bit of muscle atrophy, sometimes cramps. The afternoon is basically a Siesta, listening to music, reading, watching television.

During this period, he would video-chat with his children every day, and the children would ask their father why he was not back. He just said that dad was sick, and he was in recovery, and he'd be back.

With this experience, he suddenly felt that the world is very beautiful, himself and the people around him are very lucky, because the people around him are not infected. In the past, he was often absent from his work. This time, he was "head-to-head" with new pneumonia, which scared his family somewhat, and he said he treasured his time with them even more after he recovered.
